  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Gluons inside an unpolarized proton are in general linearly polarized in the direction of their transverse momentum, rendering the LHC effectively a polarized gluon collider. This polarization can be utilized in the determination of the spin and parity of the newly found Higgs-like boson. We focus here on the determination of the spin using the azimuthal Collins-Soper angle $\phi$ distribution.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
